Welcome to my profile & portfolio. In a nutshel:

• 12+ years of experience in the higher education industry in the Netherlands, United Kingdom and Moldova;
• advance knowledge in European affairs, International relations, EU diplomacy, Eastern Partnership democratization, diaspora as civil society as well as qualitative methodology and interviewing
• 4+ problem-based teaching & learning, 5+ networked learning, 4+ coaching, menotring & trainer experiences.
• advance research skills and high academic rigour in delivering policy papers, briefs, analysis, commentaries, stakeholder mapping, market research products;
• 10+ years of community development experience in combination wit leadership & managerial skills;
• trained to speak in public at competitions, debates, academic and non-academic events.

I like to ask the question behind the question, look for creative solutions and connect people.

profile_positions.description:
In 2012, I co-lead Noroc Olanda as an initiative group that aimed at developing social and cultural activities for Moldovans residing in the Netherlands. As the community grew, Noroc Olanda extended its objectives and became a Foundation that, inter alia, aims at: 
•	to grow the expertise and know-how of Moldovan diaspora by developing educational activities (Scoala Sustenabilitatii, Academic Skills Café, Sofa Talks, Kompot); 
•	to increasing the level of information of Moldovans inside and outside Moldova (Sofa Talks & Kompot) – our projects encourage critical-thinking, developing a solution-oriented approach and spread democratic values; 
•	to transform aid and philanthropy into community-led change by Moldovans (Fapte Bune pe Roti campaign, crowdfunding for Ziarul de Garda, movie screenings to support artists in Moldova) - our charity campaigns are directed at helping people in need in Moldova, with the aim of contributing to a sustainable future of public health and social security system in Moldova. 

Today, together with my team, we work on our mission - to facilitate the transfer of knowhow and expertise to our home-country by implementing sustainable projects.

During this fellowship I created connections between scholars interested in EU foreign policy and diplomacy on the EaP countries and  practitioners and diplomats in Brussels. 
•  conducted research on EU diplomacy in Eastern Europe;
• organized the academic-practitioner roundtable “EU Diplomacy post-Lisbon: performance, practices and impact”; 
• coordinated a scholarly group on EU diplomacy and Eastern Europe and presented research results at conference panels.
